      "message": "[warning] Line 958: This writes `bodyOverwrite` into the embedded edition entry before verifying that the plugin response belongs to the latest edition. If an older async plugin request finishes after a newer edit, it can overwrite that historical edition entry in `loadedHistory_` and the returned update with a stale value. Only update the embedded edition when `messageId` still matches the edition commit being rendered, or build a copy and populate all edition overwrites from the current commit `pluginData` state.\n```suggestion\n    libjami::SwarmMessage copy \u003d *signalTarget;\n    for (auto\u0026 edition : copy.editions) {\n        const auto idIt \u003d edition.find(\"id\");\n        if (idIt \u003d\u003d edition.end()) {\n            continue;\n        }\n        const auto edMsgIt \u003d loadedHistory_.quickAccess.find(idIt-\u003esecond);\n        if (edMsgIt \u003d\u003d loadedHistory_.quickAccess.end()) {\n            edition.erase(\"bodyOverwrite\");\n            continue;\n        }\n        if (const auto boIt \u003d edMsgIt-\u003esecond-\u003epluginData.find(\"bodyOverwrite\");\n            boIt !\u003d edMsgIt-\u003esecond-\u003epluginData.end()) {\n            edition[\"bodyOverwrite\"] \u003d boIt-\u003esecond;\n        } else {\n            edition.erase(\"bodyOverwrite\");\n        }\n    }\n```",
