      "message": "[warning] Line 2242: Edition commits are cleared without emitting an update for their original message. For an edited message, clients render the original message containing the edition list, not the edition commit itself; after clearing the edition commit\u0027s `pluginData`, no signal is queued for the original unless the original also has `editions`. Preserve the original-message notification path when a cleared commit has `CommitKey::EDIT`.\n```suggestion\n            if (msg-\u003eeditions.empty()) {\n                msg-\u003epluginData.erase(\"bodyOverwrite\");\n                if (auto editIt \u003d msg-\u003ebody.find(CommitKey::EDIT);\n                    editIt !\u003d msg-\u003ebody.end() \u0026\u0026 !editIt-\u003esecond.empty()) {\n                    if (auto originalIt \u003d loadedHistory_.quickAccess.find(editIt-\u003esecond);\n                        originalIt !\u003d loadedHistory_.quickAccess.end()) {\n                        signalMap[editIt-\u003esecond] \u003d *originalIt-\u003esecond;\n                    }\n                } else {\n                    signalMap[id] \u003d *msg;\n                }\n            }\n```",
